ue-to-life</span> in Sketch?</h2>
    </div>
    <div class=3D"vs-question__blurb">
     =20

      <p class=3D"lead"><span class=3D"highlight">They sure are.</span> Fig=
ma forces your assets to be exported using a single color profile, or to go=
 completely unmanaged. If you=E2=80=99re using Figma in the browser, you do=
n=E2=80=99t have the option to change the color profile at all. This means =
that your end-users might see something different to what you=E2=80=99ve de=
signed.</p>

<p>Whatever you do, don=E2=80=99t let your designs down with a limited and =
inaccurate color gamut.</p>

<p><strong>With Sketch, you can assign P3 or sRGB color profiles to all of =
your assets and documents.</strong></p>

